<paragraph id="F90A36AA2504956CFF6EB111FEF787E0" blockId="7.[151,1436,1269,1535]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Newly recorded in Nova 
<collectingCountry id="81A2763A2504956CFE47B111FD9E8728" box="[495,572,1309,1335]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Scotia</collectingCountry>
. This specimen, a teneral one, was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="9D244B5B2504956CFBC2B111FAB28728" author="Wright" box="[1130,1296,1309,1335]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" refString="Wright, B. (1989) The Fauna of Sable Island. Nova Scotia Museum Curatorial Report, 68, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1989">
Wright (
<number id="4F7D248D2504956CFB63B111FAAA8728" box="[1227,1288,1309,1335]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="3EB54D292504956CFA91B111FF1F8741" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBC1EAB82504956CFA91B111FF1F8741" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bembidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nr. 
<taxonomicName id="3EB54D292504956CFEBAB149FE578740" authority="Lindroth. Its" authorityName="Lindroth. Its" box="[274,501,1349,1375]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castor">
<emphasis id="CBC1EAB82504956CFEBAB149FEF98741" box="[274,347,1349,1374]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">castor</emphasis>
Lindroth. Its
</taxonomicName>
presence on Sable Island, a 
<number id="4F7D248D2504956CFCEAB149FCFD8740" box="[834,863,1349,1375]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="45.0">45</number>
kilometre long sand bar located near the edge of the continental shelf, and 
<quantity id="3E4D9B4F2504956CFE6DB161FDBD8798" box="[453,543,1389,1415]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="km" value="160.0">160 km</quantity>
from the nearest point of land, is noteworthy, given that it has not been otherwise recorded in Nova 
<collectingCountry id="81A2763A2504956CFE78B199FDBF87B0" box="[464,541,1429,1455]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Scotia</collectingCountry>
. Further research at this site is required to determine its status. Found in a large variety of environments on open, wet, clayish or sandy soil. A synanthropic species (
<bibRefCitation id="9D244B5B2504956CFB52B1B1FEEB87E0" author="Larochelle" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" refString="Larochelle, A. &amp; Lariviere, M. - C. (2003) A natural history of the ground-beetles (Coleoptera: Carabidae) of America north of Mexico. Pensoft, Sofia, Bulgaria. 583 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Larochelle &amp; Larivi√®re 
<number id="4F7D248D2504956CFEA2B1E9FEEB87E0" box="[266,329,1509,1535]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
